description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an excellent opportunity for an experienced individual looking to join our care home management team at &lt;strong&gt;Malmesbury Lawn&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong&gt;Havant&lt;/strong&gt; as &lt;strong&gt;Assistant Unit Manager.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you share our person-centred values and feel you can help to make our care home a place that our residents can really call home, we would love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your strong leadership skills will ensure the effective and efficient management of the unit, as the most senior member of staff on duty, you’ll demonstrate skills for managing staff and taking responsibility for the safety and welfare of residents as well as the maintenance of the building on a day to day basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to demonstrate experience in working with older people and have at least NVQ2 in care (or equivalent), working shifts which include evenings, weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we can offer you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hampshire County Council recognises the outstanding contribution our care staff make, so we offer a generous benefits package including; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•    Access to Local Government Pension Scheme&lt;br /&gt;•    Interest free travel loans and discounts.&lt;br /&gt;•    Family friendly policies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries please contact Bill Dyet, Registered Manager on &lt;strong&gt;bill.dyet@hants.gov.uk. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
